## Version 1 Implementation

The first version of SourceDoc needs to have the following:
- Provide Sourcing of lines of code within a file
  - The extension should automatically listen for copy paste events from the user
  - For detected paste inserts, prompt the user in-editor (VS Code Quick Input) for:
    1) source (URL or free-text attribution)
    2) reason for pasting
  - Prompt handling should be serialized so multiple pastes do not open overlapping input flows
  - If the first prompt is canceled, do not record the paste entry
  - If the second prompt is canceled, still record the paste with an empty reason
  - This should visually be represented with TextEditorDecorationService to visually highlight code line(s) with markers
  - When the user hovers over the markers, a window should pop up showing:
  ```
  {
    Source: <user-entered source>
    Time: XX:XX
    Reason: <user-entered reason or empty>
  }
  ```
  - The SourceDoc webview panel should show each paste entry only after attribution input is collected
  - The webview row should include lines, time, source, and reason
